<!-- 
1. Define the Key Terms
   - Social Context
   - Participant
   - Agent
   - Authenticator
   - Hub
 -->
 
      <t>TBD</t> 
      
      <t>In this document, the key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "REQUIRED", "SHALL", 
      "SHALL NOT", "SHOULD", "SHOULD NOT", "RECOMMENDED", "MAY", and "OPTIONAL" 
      are to be  interpreted as described in <xref target="RFC2119" />.</t> 
 
      <section title="Definitions">
        <t><list style="hanging">
        <t hangText="Social Context">Definition</t>
        <t hangText="Participant">An entity, typically a person, participating
        in a shared social context.</t>
        <t hangText="Agent">The application a participant uses to interact with
        a shared social context.</t>
        <t hangText="Authenticator">A service that provides authentication and
        authorization services for both participants and their agents within 
        the shared social context.</t>
        <t hangText="Hub">A service that acts as the definitive source for 
        all information relating to a particular social context. All participants
        and agents use the Hub to publish and receive information relating to 
        the social context. </t>
        </list></t>
      </section>
 
